As you may have noticed, our Travis builds fail more often than not. That's due to our specs running in parallel, which slow down one another since (I suppose) we're on a single-core machine.

So, the important changes which we're going to introduce with this PR are:
- Set concurrency to `1` when we're on Travis;
- Use `sudo: false` infrastructure;

This should lead to a much consistent test result across builds (hopefully reducing spurious errors).

_Side note: once we manage to make specs working flawlessly on Linux, things should get much faster (and, in addition, we get caching for free)._

My plugin was previously loading bootstrap.less via an import statement like so:

``` css
@import "bootstrap.less";
```

I updated to 0.192 and this behavior was broken - bootstrap.less could not be found.  I implemented a quick hack by depending on bootstrap in my package.json and importing bootstrap.less the stupid way:

``` css
@import "../node_modules/bootstrap/less/bootstrap.less";
```

Less was built, but the command palette was gone about half the time.  

Including a different/external version of bootstrap may not be supported behavior, but relying on the bootstrap atom ships is problematic.  For that matter, if it is not supported, an error, warning, or documentation would be helpful.
